    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-sec">
      <h2>Creatine Gummies vs Powder — FAQ</h2>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Are creatine gummies as effective as creatine powder?</summary><p>Yes, when the dose is equivalent. Creatine monohydrate is absorbed identically regardless of delivery format. A 2021 JISSN study confirmed no difference. The critical factor is hitting 3-5g daily, not the format.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>How many creatine gummies equal one scoop of powder?</summary><p>One scoop = 5g creatine. Most gummies provide 1.5-5g per serving (2-8 gummies). Check your brand: Create = ~14 gummies for 5g; Bear Balanced = 4 gummies for 5g.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Is creatine powder cheaper than gummies?</summary><p>Yes, significantly. Powder: $0.04-$0.10 per 5g serving ($15-$36/year). Gummies: $1.00-$2.00 per equivalent dose ($365-$730/year). Powder is 10-50x cheaper.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do creatine gummies cause bloating?</summary><p>Creatine causes intracellular water retention (1-3 lbs) regardless of format — this is normal and not harmful. Gummies may cause less GI discomfort than powder consumed on an empty stomach because the creatine is pre-dissolved.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Can I load creatine with gummies?</summary><p>Technically yes, but impractical. Loading requires 20g/day (16-56 gummies at $4-$8/day). Most experts now recommend skipping loading and taking 3-5g daily — saturation is reached in 3-4 weeks either way.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>What type of creatine is in gummies?</summary><p>Most use creatine monohydrate — the most researched form with 500+ studies. Some use Creapure (premium monohydrate) or creatine HCl. We recommend monohydrate for the strongest evidence base.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take creatine gummies?</summary><p>Timing is not critical. Creatine works through chronic saturation, not acute dosing. A slight advantage exists for post-workout, but the most important factor is daily consistency at 3-5g.</p></details>
      <details class="fq"><summary>Do creatine gummies need to be cycled?</summary><p>No. Long-term studies up to 5 years show no adverse effects from continuous daily use at 3-5g. The ISSN position stand explicitly states cycling is unnecessary. Take creatine daily without breaks.</p></details>
    </section>

    <p class="fda-disc">*These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. These products are not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease. Consult your healthcare provider before starting any supplement regimen.</p>

  </div>

